1 = x - (x-1)
\vert \cos(x-1)\vert
\vert \cos x\vert
1
\begin{align*} \vert \sin 1\vert &= \vert\sin\left(x - (x-1)\right)\vert\\ &= \vert\sin x \cos(x-1) - \cos x \sin(x-1)\vert\\ &\le \vert\sin x \cos(x-1)\vert + \vert\cos x\sin(x-1)\vert\\ &\le \vert\sin x \vert + \vert\sin(x-1)\vert, \end{align*}
\sin(1) = \sin(x + (1-x)) = \sin(x)\cos(1-x)+\sin(1-x)\cos(x) \le \vert\sin(x)\vert+\vert\sin(x-1)\vert
